Early plans called for memorial plaques to be embedded into the berm, with each plaque honoring a deceased congregant.[26][23] Southeast of the church building is a memorial garden planted in 1995,[24][18] with 43 trees representing the original members of the congregation.[18] The garden, designed by Todd Williams, contains wooden plaques and a bench. The original plans called for a sculpture and a wall made of slate, which were never built.[24]